  • Field Details

    • transparency

      private boolean transparency
      Specifies whether the block has half-transparent textures (alpha between 0 and 1)

    • opaque

      private boolean opaque
      Specifies whether this block is solid. Blocks behind solid blocks don't get rendered - only set this if there is no way to see through your block. Set this to false if your texture has blank spots.

    • occluding

      private boolean occluding
      Specifies whether this block "occludes". This means light gets darker towards this blocks corners. Set this to false if your block doesn't really fill the space it is placed in - otherwise, you will get weird artifacts.

    • customModel

      private boolean customModel
      Specifies whether this block has a custom 3D model that should be used instead of the default cube model.

    • hasBlockTypeImplementation

      private boolean hasBlockTypeImplementation
      Specifies whether this block has a custom block type implementation. If this is set to true, there must be a class called (name)BlockType in the package de.oth.blocklib.world.blocks.types.

    • hasCustomRenderer

      private boolean hasCustomRenderer
      Whether this block has a custom renderer. If true, the render method in the block type will be called when rendering instead of just using the default rendering procedures. This flag requires hasBlockTypeImplementation to be set to true, since it requires a BlockType to implement the render method.

    • hasCollision

      private boolean hasCollision
      Whether this block has collision. Set this to false for blocks that the player or any NPCs should not collide with.

    • isFluid

      private boolean isFluid

    • populationType

      private BlockMetaData.PopulationType populationType
      The populating type of this block. Set this to any of the enum values for this block to be populated into the world automatically, according to the biomOccurrence value.

    • biomOccurrence

      private short[] biomOccurrence
      The list of biome IDs this block should be populated in.
      See Also:
      populationType

    • maxHitPoints

      private float maxHitPoints
      How many HP a block (maximal) has. Used for how long it takes to break a block and also how to texture the crack. in seconds / 10.0

    • blockStrips

      private java.util.List<BlockMetaData.BlockStrip> blockStrips
      A list of resource generation definitions, used to generate ores when generating the world.
